#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:56
msgid "Latch States"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:58
msgid ""
"The latch mechanism has two major states: *open* and *closed*. In the "
"*closed* state (default), the clipboard is secured to the base, whereas in "
"the *open* state, the clipboard can be removed by a user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:62
msgid ""
"The latch can additionally be locked and, correspondingly, unlocked, which "
"can influence the detachment procedure. Specifically, this locking mechanism "
"is intended to prevent the dGPU, positioned in the base of the device, from "
"being hot-unplugged while in use. More details can be found in the "
"documentation for the detachment procedure below. By default, the latch is "
"unlocked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:70
msgid "Detachment Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:72
msgid ""
"Note that the detachment process is governed fully by the EC. The "
"``surface_dtx`` driver only relays events from the EC to user-space and "
"commands from user-space to the EC, i.e. it does not influence this process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:76
msgid ""
"The detachment process is started with the user pressing the *detach* button "
"on the base of the device or executing the ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_REQUEST`` "
"IOCTL. Following that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:80
msgid ""
"The EC turns on the indicator led on the detach-button, sends a *detach-"
"request* event (``SDTX_EVENT_REQUEST``), and awaits further instructions/"
"commands. In case the latch is unlocked, the led will flash green. If the "
"latch has been locked, the led will be solid red"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:85
msgid ""
"The event is, via the ``surface_dtx`` driver, relayed to user-space, where "
"an appropriate user-space daemon can handle it and send instructions back to "
"the EC via IOCTLs provided by this driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:89
msgid ""
"The EC waits for instructions from user-space and acts according to them. If "
"the EC does not receive any instructions in a given period, it will time out "
"and continue as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:93
msgid ""
"If the latch is unlocked, the EC will open the latch and the clipboard can "
"be detached from the base. This is the exact behavior as without this driver "
"or any user-space daemon. See the ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_CONFIRM`` description "
"below for more details on the follow-up behavior of the EC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:98
msgid ""
"If the latch is locked, the EC will *not* open the latch, meaning the "
"clipboard cannot be detached from the base. Furthermore, the EC sends an "
"cancel event (``SDTX_EVENT_CANCEL``) detailing this with the cancel reason "
"``SDTX_DETACH_TIMEDOUT`` (see :ref:`events` for details)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:103
msgid ""
"Valid responses by a user-space daemon to a detachment request event are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:105
msgid ""
"Execute ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_REQUEST``. This will immediately abort the "
"detachment process. Furthermore, the EC will send a detach-request event, "
"similar to the user pressing the detach-button to cancel said process (see "
"below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:110
msgid ""
"Execute ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_CONFIRM``. This will cause the EC to open the "
"latch, after which the user can separate clipboard and base."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:113
msgid ""
"As this changes the latch state, a *latch-status* event "
"(``SDTX_EVENT_LATCH_STATUS``) will be sent once the latch has been opened "
"successfully. If the EC fails to open the latch, e.g. due to hardware error "
"or low battery, a latch-cancel event (``SDTX_EVENT_CANCEL``) will be sent "
"with the cancel reason indicating the specific failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:119
msgid ""
"If the latch is currently locked, the latch will automatically be unlocked "
"before it is opened."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:122
msgid ""
"Execute ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_HEARTBEAT``. This will reset the internal "
"timeout. No other actions will be performed, i.e. the detachment process "
"will neither be completed nor canceled, and the EC will still be waiting for "
"further responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:127
msgid ""
"Execute ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_CANCEL``. This will abort the detachment process, "
"similar to ``SDTX_IOCTL_LATCH_REQUEST``, described above, or the button "
"press, described below. A *generic request* event (``SDTX_EVENT_REQUEST``) "
"is send in response to this. In contrast to those, however, this command "
"does not trigger a new detachment process if none is currently in progress."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:134
msgid ""
"Do nothing. The detachment process eventually times out as described in "
"point 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:137
msgid "See :ref:`ioctls` for more details on these responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:139
msgid ""
"It is important to note that, if the user presses the detach button at any "
"point when a detachment operation is in progress (i.e. after the EC has sent "
"the initial *detach-request* event (``SDTX_EVENT_REQUEST``) and before it "
"received the corresponding response concluding the process), the detachment "
"process is canceled on the EC-level and an identical event is being sent. "
"Thus a *detach-request* event, by itself, does not signal the start of the "
"detachment process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../driver-api/surface_aggregator/clients/dtx.rst:147
msgid ""
"The detachment process may further be canceled by the EC due to hardware "
"failures or a low clipboard battery. This is done via a cancel event "
"(``SDTX_EVENT_CANCEL``) with the corresponding cancel reason."
msgstr ""

